  "name": "RPlog_Finding_Lynae",
  "title": "Finding Lynae",
  "summary": "In a rain-soaked plaza on Ord Mantell, the dying Dareus and the mercenary Axel Vichten, accompanied by combat droids, track down Dr. Lynae Cassius, who is finishing old business under the protection of the NRI agents Enb'Zik and his Horansi wife Snarl. A tense standoff unfolds as the Sullustan and Horansi try to extract Lynae, suspicious of the newcomers, while the embittered Cade silently recognizes Lynae as the supposed traitor responsible for his brother's death. Lynae defuses the confrontation, insisting she is no prisoner and dismissing her Republic escort, just as Darth Malign himself arrives to add weight to the recruitment pitch. Aboard Lynae's ship the Red Sky, Dareus and Axel make their offer over cups of caf: command of a capital ship in their breakaway Sith battle group, the Predator and the Embrace, answering only to Malign. They arrive at the black-painted Star Destroyer Predator, where Lynae, proud of her bloody past and weighing the offer carefully, asks only that her fallen comrade Yoseph's remains be cremated and cast into space before retiring to consider.",
